com.sleepycat.client

Class SMultiplePairs

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.sleepycat.client.SMultiplePairs
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    SDatabaseEntryBase
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    SMultipleKeyDataEntry, SMultipleRecnoDataEntry

    public abstract class SMultiplePairs
extends java.lang.Object
implements SDatabaseEntryBase
    An abstract class representing a container that holds multiple key/data SDatabaseEntry pairs. Use one of the concrete subclasses depending on whether you need:
    • multiple key / data item pairs: SMultipleKeyDataEntry
    • multiple record number / data item pairs: SMultipleRecnoDataEntry

      • setBatchSize

        public void setBatchSize(int batchSize)
        When used as an output argument to a database or cursor get() call, set the amount of data (in total bytes) to be returned.

        This method is only advisory. The exact amount of data returned may be more or less than the amount specified.

        Parameters:
        batchSize - the amount of data to be returned in a single get() call

      • next

        public boolean next(SDatabaseEntry key,
                    SDatabaseEntry data)
        Get the next key/data pair in the returned set. This method may only be called after a successful call to a SDatabase or SCursor get method with this object as the data parameter.

        When used with the Queue and Recno access methods, data.getData() will return null for deleted records

        Parameters:
        key - an entry that is set to refer to the next key element in the returned set
        data - an entry that is set to refer to the next data element in the returned set
        Returns:
        indicates whether a value was found. A return of false indicates that the end of the set was reached.
